<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Indonesia-Bomb Found </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bomb found in Indonesia's tallest building
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) - Police defused a small bomb that was
discovered in Indonesia's tallest building, newspapers reported
Saturday.
	   The explosive device was found by a security guard at 3 a.m.
Friday near a toilet door on the ground floor of the 50-story Wisna
BNI 46 tower, authorities said.
	   There were no claims of responsibility and police declined to
speculate on who may have planted the bomb.
	   The device was placed in a 10 by 20 centimeter (4 by 8 inches)
box and was equipped with a timer, The Jakarta Post quoted Col.
Jacky Uly, commander of the national police bomb squad, as saying.
	   The bomb was set to explode at 3 p.m. Friday, 12 hours after it
was found, Jacky said.
	   The office tower houses operations of Bank Indonesia, the
central bank, which has been at the center of efforts to revive the
nation's paralyzed economy.
	   The city's American Club, a fashionable restaurant and the
offices of about 100 companies are also in the building.
</TEXT>
