<HEADLINE>
Storm reaches hurricane strength off Mexico's Pacific coast
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES location, strength of hurricane. At 0400 GMT,
hurricane was near 12.5 N., 103.8 W &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MEXICO CITY (AP) _ Hurricane Howard continued building strength
Friday in the Pacific Ocean, but remained far off the Mexican
coast.
	   As of 0400 GMT Saturday, Hurricane Howard was 400 miles (640
kilometers) south-southwest of Acapulco, moving west-northwest at
12 1/2 mph (20 kph), the U.S. National Weather Service reported. It
had sustained winds of 98 mph (160 kilometers) and gusts of 121 mph
(195 kph) and was expected to continue building strength until
Sunday.
	   Authorities closed the Acapulco port Thursday and warned ships
to be cautious of high waves along the southwestern Mexican coast. 	   
</TEXT>
