<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Japan-Video Arrests </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Japanese arrested filming Thai women with see-through camera
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Two Japanese tourists were arrested
videotaping Thai women at a shopping mall with a ``see-through''
video camera hidden in a shopping bag, police said Saturday.
	   Toshinobu Oinuma and his brother Toru, both residents of Tokyo,
were arrested Friday evening and charged with attempting to produce
a pornographic video.
	   Department stores have been pulling off their shelves the models
of video cameras that allow filming in extremely low light after
they were found to also see through clothing.
	   Police said the video contained more than 60 minutes of scenes
in which young Thai women's bodies could be seen through their
clothing, although not very clearly.
	   Police believe the video was intended for commercial purposes in
Japan.
	   The accused will stand trial in Bangkok. It will be up to a
court to send them back to Japan or serve jail time in Thailand,
said the officer.
</TEXT>
