r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Thailand-PoliceMurder     08-22 0147
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Police Murders </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Warrant issued for fourteen Thai police charged with murder
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Bangkok, Thailand (AP) _ Thai authorities have issued arrest
warrants for 14 police officers suspected of murdering three men,
the police department said Saturday.
	   The officers were charged with premeditated murder and the
cover-up of their crime, said a police official, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
	   The charged detectives are from a special operations unit based
in Prachuab Khiri Khan, 230 kilometers (143 miles) south of
Bangkok. The most senior officer being sought is Col. Boonchoke
Pariyathin, who could not be reached for comment.
	   Police say the three men were killed at a check point near Hua
Hin, a popular seaside resort in the province. They would not
comment on a possible motivation. Their charred corpses were found
by a bush behind a school. 	   
</TEXT>
