CHINA: DISEASE - APTV updates the situation with China's continuing
flood crisis which is now bringing disease to areas under water.
(EXPECTED FIRST RUN ASIA PACIFIC LATE 0715)
----
PHILIPPINES: AQUINO - APTV expects a package from Manila marking the
15th anniversary of the assassination of Benigno Aquino which
started the downfall of President Ferdinand Marcos' regime. Material
will include an interview with Aquino's widow and former president,
Corazon Aquino. (EXPECTED FIRST RUN ASIA PACIFIC LATE 0715GMT)
----
THAILAND: INDONESIA - APTV expects coverage of protests outside the
Indonesian embassy in Bangkok. The demonstrations are over attacks
on ethnic Chinese in the wake of Indonesia's economic problems.
(EXPECTED FIRST RUN ASIA PACIFIC LATE 0715GMT)
----
THAILAND: MYANMAR - APTV will have coverage of a protest outside
Myanmar's embassy drawing attention to the military government's
failure to convene parliament. (EXPECTED FIRST RUN ASIA PACIFIC LATE
0715GMT)
----
TAIWAN: ARTIST - APTV has a report on an artist in Taiwan whose
explosive style has fired up a local art museum to look like a
dragon.
(EXPECTED FIRST RUN ASIA PACIFIC LATE 0715GMT)
----
US: TITANIC - APTV has pictures of the recovery of a large section
of the hull of the sunken luxury cruise liner, Titanic. It's said to
be the largest section of the Titanic ever recovered. (EXPECTED
FIRST RUN ASIA PACIFIC LATE 0715GMT)
----
PAKISTAN: INJURED - APTV is expecting pictures from Peshawar of
people injured in the U-S military strike on neighboring
Afghanistan.
(EXPECTED F-L-A-S-H AFTER 0830GMT)

RUNNING:  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
