<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Boy Bank Robber </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Teen accused of trying to rob Thai bank
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ A 14-year-old Thai boy is suspected of
attempting to rob a bank Saturday allegedly to obtain money for
drugs, Thai television reported.
	   After failing to break into an automatic teller machine, the
boy, whose name was not released by police, threw a rock through
the door of a bank in Bangkok, they said.
	   Police responded to the bank's alarm and arrested the boy, whom
they said appeared to have been sniffing glue.
	   The boy told Independent Television that he broke into the bank
to search for money and valuables because he was desperate to buy
drugs and to pay for his way home.
	   He said he wanted to return to his family in Phangna province,
590 kilometers (366 miles) south of Bangkok.
	   Police said the boy appeared to be a drug addict. He would be
sent to a foster home after an investigation, a police officer told
ITV.
</TEXT>
