w2165 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Japan-Turbulence     08-22 0154
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Japan-Turbulence </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Flight from Guam to Tokyo hits turbulence, minor injuries
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ A Continental Micronesia jet hit air turbulence on
a flight from the U.S. territory of Guam to Tokyo on Saturday,
slightly injuring two or three people aboard, police said.
	   Minoru Matsumura, an airport police spokesman, said the injured
headed for a clinic on their own after arriving on Flight 967 at
New Tokyo International Airport at Narita on Saturday evening.
	   Narita is 65 kilometers (40 miles), northeast of Tokyo.
	   The spokesman said it was not immediately clear where the flight
hit the turbulence, exactly how many were injured or whether those
hurt were passengers or crew members.
	   In December, sudden turbulence hit a United Airlines jet as it
was flying over the Pacific from Tokyo to Honolulu. A 32-year-old
woman died of a head injury and more than 100 others were hurt.
	   (km-jc) 	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
