<HEADLINE>
First-stage champion Iwata loses opener in second stage
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ First-stage champion Jubilo Iwata blew a 2-0
first-half lead as Yokohama Marinos came from behind to win in
extra-time in an opening game of the second stage of Japan's
professional soccer J-League Saturday.
	   Yokohama scored two goals after the interval and substitute
Sotaro Yasunaga kicked a sudden-death goal 22 minutes into extra
time for the 3-2 away victory.
	   Visiting Shimizu S-Pulse, which placed second in the first stage
on goal differences, beat Yokohama Flugels 4-2. Junji Nishizawa
headed home to break a 2-2 tie in the 60th minute, followed by
Kenta Hasegawa's goal 13 minutes later.
	   Kashima Antlers, last season's first-stage winner, got off to a
good start with a 3-1 victory over JEF United Ichihara. Kashima
finished fifth in the first stage.
	   The second stage extends through Nov. 14. If two teams emerge as
stage winners, they will have to play off for the league
championship in a two-leg series Nov. 21 and 28.
