<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Somalia-Poisoned Water </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
At least 15 said to die from tainted water
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MODADISHU, Somalia (AP) _ At least 15 people were reported dead
and another three dozen seriously sickened after drinking water
that had been hauled in a barrel apparently tainted with toxic
material.
	   Sketchy reports on Saturday said the poisonings occurred after
nomads in a dry area asked travelers to fill the barrel from wells
that were several days walk away. Those who drank the water later
suffered convulsions, and some died, according to the reports.
	   A militia commander in the area contacted by radio, Col.
Abdirizak Hassan Awl, said a few of those who were sickened managed
to reach the town of Abudwaq to seek help, and told officials there
what had happened.
	   Awl said the barrel had apparently previously contained toxic
material, possibly ingredients for fertilizer.
	   The incident occurred in the central region of Galgudud, about
200 miles (320 km) northeast of the capital, Mogadishu.
 &UR; (stgr-lk)
</TEXT>
