<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1098 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Tropical storm Bonnie strengthened to a hurricane overnight as
it continued its west-northwest movement away from the local
islands. Some lingering rain bands and stiff southerly winds on the
back edge of Bonnie continued to affect Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands. Scattered showers and thunderstorms moved north to
northeast on shore over the south coasts of the islands. The
heaviest rain was detected over the southeast and eastern interior
of Puerto Rico where Doppler estimated around 4 inches in places
across the municipalities of Guayama, Arroyo, Patillas, Caguas and
Salinas. This prompted an urban and small stream flood advisory and
a flash flood watch for the rivers across the eastern interior to
southeast.
	   Clouds and rain bands will continue to affect Puerto Rico and
the U.S. Virgin Islands today. Most of the showers and
thunderstorms will move across the islands this morning producing
intermittent showers and thunderstorms, some with heavy rain and
gusty winds. The winds will remain southerly up to 20 to 25 mph and
gusty through the day. Skies will brighten this afternoon as Bonnie
moves farther away from the local islands and drier air begins to
move in through Sunday.
	   Seas across the Atlantic coastal waters will remain rough as
northwest to west swells persist from Bonnie. Also fresh to strong
southerly winds will keep seas high in the Caribbean as well.
Therefore a small craft advisory will remain in effect across both
the Atlantic and the Caribbean waters for today.
	   The next tropical wave over the Atlantic located 700 miles east
of the Windward Islands will approach our local area by late Monday
into Tuesday.
 &UR; San Juan and north sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 40 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms, mainly morning. High 85 to 95. Wind
south 15 to 20 mph and gusty.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind southeast around 10 mph.
	   Sunday ... Mostly sunny morning. Partly cloudy and hot
afternoon. A 20 percent chance of showers. Slight chance of a
thunderstorm. High 90 to 95. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; East sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 50 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms ... Mainly morning. High from 70 to 75
mountains to 85 to 90 low elevations. Wind south 15 to 20 mph and
gusty.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Sunday ... Partly cloudy morning with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Mostly sunny afternoon. High around 85. Wind southeast
around 15 mph.
 &UR; Ponce and south sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 50 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms, mainly morning. High 80 to 90. Wind
south 15 to 20 mph and gusty.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Generally fair west. Low 70 to 80. Wind southeast to east
around 10 mph.
	   Sunday ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Isolated afternoon thunderstorms, mainly inland. High 80 to 90.
Wind southeast near 15 mph.
 &UR; Mayaguez and west sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 40 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind becoming south 10 to
20 mph and gusty.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of evening
showers and thunderstorms. Becoming fair by midnight. Low around
75. Wind southeast 5 to 10 mph.
	   Sunday ... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms.
High 85 to 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph except variable along
the coast in the afternoon.
 &UR; Interior sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 50 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High from near 75 mountains to 80 to 90
lower elevations. Wind south 15 to 20 mph and gusty.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 65 to 75. Wind southeast near 10 mph.
	   Sunday ... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms.
High from near 75 mountains to 80 to 90 lower elevations. Wind
southeast near 15 mph.
 &UR; St. Thomas, St. John and St. Croix
	   Today ... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 60 percent chance of
showers or thunderstorms ... Mainly morning. High 85 to 90. Wind
south to southeast 15 to 25 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind southeast around 10 mph.
	   Sunday ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
High near 90. Wind southeast near 15 mph.
 &UR; Puerto Rico and U.S. Virgin Islands waters
	   Synopsis ... Hurricane Bonnie continues to move west-northwest
out of local coastal waters keeping fresh to strong southerly flow
on back end through Saturday. Bonnie will continue to produce
moderate northwest to west swells to affect the north and west
coastal waters through Sunday.
 &UR; Atlantic waters
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon ... Wind south to southeast 15 to 25 kt. Seas 6
to 8 ft in northwest swells. Scattered showers and thunderstorms.
	   Tonight ... Wind southeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 5 to 7 ft in west
swells. Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Sunday ... Wind southeast to east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 5 to 7 in
west swells. Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
 &UR; Caribbean waters
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon ... Wind south to southeast 15 to 25 kt. Seas 5
to 7 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight ... Wind southeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 5 to 6 ft. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Sunday ... Wind southeast to east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
 &UR; Caribbean waters
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon ... Wind southwest to south 15 to 25 kt. Seas 6
to 7 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight ... Wind south to southeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 5 to 6 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Sunday ... Wind southeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft. Scattered
showers. Isolated thunderstorms. 	   
