r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Baseball-Japan     08-22 0222
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-Japan Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dragons defeats BayStars 4-3
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Leo Gomez and Kazuki Inoue hit a pair of doubles in
the third inning to score a winning run as Chunichi Dragons beat
the Central League's front-running Yokohama BayStars 4-3 at
Yokohama Saturday.
	   Gomez, formerly with Chicago Cubs, went 3 for 4 before a crowd
of 30,000 people. The BayStars are now three games ahead of the
Dragons.
	   At Hiroshima, Tomoaki Kanemoto smashed a pair of home runs,
including the day's second homer in the bottom of 11th inning,
giving the Hiroshima Toyo Carp a 6-4 win over the Yomiuri Giants.
	   Hideki Matsui blasted a home home run for the Giants. Matsui has
28 home runs and lead the league.
	   The Yakult Swallows edged the Hanshin Tigers 3-2 at Osaka Dome.
	   In the Pacific League, hurler Rob Mattson scattered three hits
in 8 1/3 innings, helping the Kintetsu Buffaloes to top the
front-running Nippon Ham Fighters 5-3 at Tokyo Dome. Mattson
previously played in the Mexican League.
	   In Chiba, Brian Williams gave up only five hits and went the
distance, helping the Fukuoka Daiei Hawks beat the China Lotte
Marines 5-1. The Hawks extended their winning streak to three.
	   At Seibu Stadium, the Seibu Lions beat the Orix BlueWave on
Fumiya Nichiguchi's five-hit, 2-0 shutout.
 &UR; (km)
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Sports-Baseball-Japan Roundup; CT:s; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
