w2462 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-APNewsDigest     08-22 0945
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AP News Digest,0946 </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 1700 GMT:
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _US-SUPERPOWER SUPERENEMY. Bin Laden fought Soviets, now
Americans.
	   _SUDAN-WAR AT HOME. Sudanese rally around country after attacks.
	   _US-CLINTON INVESTIGATION. Clinton offers explanations for
charges.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   EDGARTOWN, Massachusetts _ Turning up the fight against
terrorism a notch, President Bill Clinton moves to shut down the
financial pipeline feeding Osama bin Laden's network. US-BOMBINGS.
Lead expected by 2100 GMT. By Sonya Ross. AP Photos LHR101
KHT107,108.
	   WASHINGTON _ From hideouts in Afghanistan's rugged mountains,
Osama bin Laden used his wealth to create cells of fighters to
cleanse the Islamic country of its Soviet occupiers. Now, U.S.
missile attacks in response to terrorist bombs in Africa have
thrust him into war with an even stronger superpower. US-SUPERPOWER
SUPERENEMY. Expected by 2100 GMT. By Donna Abu-Nasr. AP Photo NY186
	   KHARTOUM, Sudan _ American officials call their missile strike
on a chemical plant in the Sudanese capital a blow against states
that support terrorism. For Sudan's government, it has provided a
rare opportunity to rally its people around the flag. SUDAN-WAR AT
HOME. Expected by 2000 GMT. By Anthony Shadid. AP Photos 101-108.
	   NAIROBI, Kenya _ Three men in the custody of Kenyan authorities
confess that they pretended to be fish mongers as a cover to case
the U.S. Embassy while planning a devastating car bombing,
according to a newspaper report Saturday. EMBASSY BOMBINGS. Lead
has moved. By Laura King. AP Photo NAI101.
	   WITH:
	   _US-CRUISE MISSILES. The Tomahawk cruise missiles that slammed
into suspected terrorist targets where part of a strategy to keep
American fighters out of harm's way while bringing pinpoint
destruction on the enemy. Expected by 2100 GMT.
	   _ALBANIA-ARRESTS. Albanians arrest 10 in anti-terrorist
operation. Has moved.
	   _SUDAN-US. Sudanese rally against U.S. strikes. Has moved.
	   _PAKISTAN-US-BOMBINGS. Militant group denies attacked bases were
terrorist camps. AP Photo ISL101. Has moved.
	   WASHINGTON _ As details of a remarkable week of grand jury
testimony by President Bill Clinton and a young former intern
filter into the public domain, the Clinton camp is slowly unwinding
a fragile string of explanations to protect him against charges of
perjury and obstruction of justice. US-CLINTON-INVESTIGATION. Lead
has moved. By Ron Fournier. AP Photo MVY101.
	   GOMA, Congo _ Rebels pushing within 30 kilometers (18 miles) of
Congo's capital say Saturday they downed two warplanes allied with
embattled President Laurent Kabila's loyalist forces. CONGO-REBELS.
Lead has moved. By Hrvoje Hranski. AP Photos KIN101-104.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _CONGO-PEACE TALKS. Congo, Zimbabwe skip peace talks.
	   BEIJING _ Weeks of high waters crack soggy dikes protecting
cities along the Yangtze River on Saturday, and soldiers in the
northeast fight to stop a breached levee by China's largest oil
field. CHINA-FLOODS. Lead has moved. By Charles Hutzler.
	   OMAGH, Northern Ireland _ Hundreds of thousands, perhaps
millions, fall silent Saturday across Ireland in remembrance of 28
people slain in Northern Ireland's deadliest terrorist attack.
NORTHERN IRELAND. Lead has moved. By Shawn Pogatchnik. AP Photos
XMA101,XOGH103-105, LON104.
	   SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic _ Caribbean nations sign a
trade pact Saturday at a 16-nation summit overshadowed by the
presence of Cuban leader Fidel Castro. CARIBBEAN SUMMMIT. Lead
expected by 2000 GMT. By Dan Perry. AP Photos staffing.
	   BONN, Germany _ The opposition Social Democrats kick off the
final stretch of Germany's election campaign Saturday by blaming
Chancellor Helmut Kohl for record joblessness. GERMANY-SOCIAL
DEMOCRATS. Has moved. By Tony Czuczka.
	   MEXICO CITY _ The Mexican government is preparing for some
fiscal belt-tightening in the face of global economic turmoil and
stagnation in oil prices. MEXICO-BUDGET. Has moved. By Adolfo
Garza. AP Photos MO101-102.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: On Sunday, Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong
gives `state-of-the-republic' speech.
 &UR; FEATURES MOVED:
	   _FEA-EGYPT-MAHFOUZ SPEAKS OUT. Egypt's Nobel laureate bares his
soul _ and stirs a storm. AP Photo CAI101.
	   _FEA-PARAGUAY-NO HONEYMOON. Political honeymoon for Paraguay's
new president lasted only days. AP Photo NY108.
	   _TRAV-INDONESIA-TIMOR TOURISM _ As political reform sweeps
Indonesia, local officials hope tensions will ease, tempting
foreign divers and hikers to check out its coral reefs, white-sand
beaches and rocky hills. AP Photos NY303-NY305.
	   _TRAV-FRENCH PERFUME _ Tourists these days are following their
noses to a decidedly French institution, the perfume museum. AP
Photos PAR121-122.
	   _TRAV-US-WILD RAPIDS _ Some 250,000 people a year raft the New,
Gauley and three other West Virginia rivers, ranging in difficulty
from Class I for beginners to Class VI for experts. AP Photo NY306.
	   With TRAV-WILD RAPIDS-TIPS.
	   _ TRAV-US-LAKE GEORGE _ Lake George in the Adirondacks, called
the ``Queen of American Lakes,'' is a popular tourist destination
with numerous campgrounds, amusement parks and hotels. AP Photo
NY307.
	   With TRAV-LAKE GEORGE-TIPS.
	   _TRAV-Travel Briefs.
	   YOUR QUERIES: The Associated Press World Service editors in
charge are Ravi Nessman and Bruce Rule. Questions and story
requests to The Associated Press World Service are welcome. Contact
your local AP bureau or the AP International Desk in New York,
telephone (1) 212-621-1650, fax (1) 212-621-5449. 	   
</TEXT>
