<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Moscow-Cathedral </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Moscow mayor: No more money this year for Christ the Savior church
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Moscow Mayor Yuri Luzhkov said Saturday there was
no more money this year to finish construction of the landmark
Christ the Savior Cathedral because of Russia's financial crisis.
	   The grandiose cathedral, which dominates central Moscow's
skyline, has been rebuilt over the past three years to replicate
one destroyed by Soviet dictator Josef Stalin in 1931.
	   The original cathedral, designed to celebrate Russia's victory
over Napoleon in 1812, was consecrated in 1883 after four decades
of construction.
	   ``The situation is very difficult, but not disastrous,'' Luzhkov
said, according to the ITAR-Tass news agency. ``There are
possibilities for continuing the construction program.''
	   (ls) 	   
</TEXT>
