Central Asian officials meet in Tashkent
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TASHKENT, Uzbekistan (AP) _ The defense and foreign ministers
from the former Soviet republics in Central Asia held talks behind
closed doors on Saturday about the fighting in Afghanistan.
	   No details were released about the meeting of ministers from
Uzbekistan, Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan.
	   The countries are concerned that if the Taliban Islamic army
gains full control of Afghanistan there could be a influx of
refugees and weapons across their borders.
