LONDON: at Kilmarnock
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Charlton 5, Southampton 0 (1-0) &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   1-0 John Robinson fired the Addicks ahead in the 3rd minute,
turning home a cross vie the inside of the post. Neil Redfearn,
signed from Barnsley during the summer, hit the second in the first
minute of second half before Mendonca hit three goals in the 65th,
81st and 90th. 16,488.
 &UR; Chelsea 1, Newcastle 1 (1-1) &QC; 
	   Celestine Babayaro scored his first goal for the club in the
23rd minute after Gustavo Poyet's shot had been blocked on the line
by Stuart Pearce. Andreas Andersson hit the equalizer two minutes
before half time from a tight angle from Alan Shearer's headed
pass. 34,795.
 &UR; Derby 0, Wimbledon 0 &QC; 
	   Referee Jeff Winter infuriated the hosts by disallowing a late
Paulo Wanchope ``goal.'' Two minutes into injury time, the lanky
Costa Rican back-headed Lee Carsley's deep cross past the Dons
Scottish international goalkeeper, Neil Sullivan, and ran to
celebrate only for Winter to rule out the goal presumably for a
foul. 25,747.
 &UR; Leicester 2, Everton 0 (2-0) &QC; 
	   The Foxes went ahead after 11 minutes when Theo Zagorakis'
through ball found Tony Cottee in space on the edge of the area and
he placed the ball expertly beyond 'keeper Thomas Myhre. Muzzy
Izzet added the second in the 38th by turning in Steve Guppy's
cross. 21,037.
 &UR; Liverpool 0, Arsenal 0 &QC; 
	   Brad Friedel made a great blocking save to keep out shot from
Nicolas Anelka and Ray Parlour failed to turn in the rebound from
in front of goal for an amazing miss. Friedel also saved from
Anelka early in second half and Marc Overmars looked certain to
score a late winner for Arsenal when he rounded Friedel but Jamie
Carragher got back to rescue his team with a tackle. 44,429.
 &UR; Nottingham Forest 1, Coventry 0 (0-0) &QC; 
	   Steve Stone, who missed most of last season through injury, shot
home from edge of area in 51st minute for the only goal of the
game. 22,546,
 &UR; Tottenham 0, Sheffield Wednesday 3 (0-2) &QC; 
	   Peter Atherton's header from Wim Jonk's free kick put Wednesday
ahead in the 26th minute. Ten minutes before half time, Paolo Di
Canio made it 2-0 at second attempt after Ian Walker's initial
save. Andy Hinchcliffe scored the third in the 78th minute from a
20-meter (yard) free kick. 32,129.
 &UR; West Ham 0, Manchester United 0 &QC; 
	   United claimed a penalty after only three minutes when Ryan
Giggs was held back by Neil Ruddock but it was waved away. The Reds
created few chances after that and neither did the Hammers, who
badly missed injured Ian Wright. 26,039.
</TEXT>
