<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Women-Russia-Denmark,0222 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Denmark qualifies for third straight World Cup
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SELYATINO, Russia (AP) _ Gitte Krogh and Lene Jensen sent
Denmark to its third straight Women's World Cup finals on Saturday,
scoring in the 52nd and 81st minutes to give it a 2-1 victory over
Russia on Saturday.
	   The victory before a crowd of 300 clinched the European Group
Four title for Denmark and made it the eighth team to qualify for
the 16-nation field.
	   Denmark joined Sweden, Italy and defending champion Norway from
Europe as qualifiers. Russia already had clinched a place in one of
two, two-leg playoffs to determine Europe's other two berths.
	   Finland and European champion Germany also have clinched playoff
berths. Ukraine and Iceland are still in contention for the final
playoff spot.
	   North Korea, China, Japan and Brazil have qualified from Asia
and South America for the June 19-July 10, 1999, event. The host
United States, which is the only nation to get an automatic berth,
gives the tournament more than half of its participants.
	   The Danes played more confidently through but took seven minutes
into the second half before Krogh ended the stalemate.
	   Jensen secured the victory with nine minutes remaining. Galina
Komarov scored Russia's consolation goal in the 90th.
</TEXT>
