<SLUG> BC-AP-APTV: 1800 Outlook,0970 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
APTV'S 1800 OUTLOOK FOR SATURDAY AUGUST 22, 1998
</HEADLINE>
----
For Planner / Newsdesk use - stories expected to move in the next 12
hours  &QC;  &QC; 
----
EXPECTED:  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
US: SECURITY - Heightened security measures in the wake of U-S
military strikes on suspected terrorist sites in Afghanistan and
Sudan have been put in place in the American capital.  APTV's
package will included these security measures, Bill Clinton's
address to the nation, comments from White House press secretary
Mike McCurry and pictures from Martha's Vineyard where Bill Clinton
has returned to resume his holidays. (FIRST EXPECTED RUN 1830 NORTH
AMERICA UPDATE)
----
US: VIETNAM MASS - Basilica of National Shrine of the Immaculate
Conception will host an estimated 5,000 Vietnamese Catholics from
across the U-S for the conclusion of 200th anniversary of Virgin
Mary's apparitions to persecuted Christians in La Vang forest,
formerly part of South Vietnam.  APTV will have coverage. (FIRST
EXPECTED RUN 1945 ASIA PACIFIC EARLY)
----
BOLIVIA: ANNIVERSARY - Hundreds of protestors marked the 27th
anniversary of current president, Hugo Banzer's coup d'etat in 1971
and remembered those who disappeared during his dictatorship.  APTV
will have coverage. (FIRST EXPECTED RUN 1900 LATIN AMERICA)
----
COLOMBIA: HOSTAGES - Colombian President, Andres Pastrana, is
analysing a proposal from the rebel group F-A-R-C to exchange
captured soldiers for imprisoned guerrillas.  The leader of the
F-A-R-C offered on Wednesday to swap more than two hundred soldiers
and police captured over the past eight months.  APTV will have
coverage.  (FIRST EXPECTED RUN 2130 LATIN AMERICA UPDATE)
----
DOM REP: SUMMIT - APTV will continue its coverage of the five day
summit of 15 Caribbean leaders that is underway in the Dominican
capital Santo Domingo.  (FIRST EXPECTED RUN 2130 LATIN AMERICA
UPDATE)
----
KOSOVO: FUNERAL -  As fighting continues in the southern regions of
Kosovo with causalities on both sides, APTV will have pictures of
the funeral of 29 year old Avni Saci who was killed yesterday by
police in an unclarified incident in Drenica.  Pictures also include
Kosovo Liberation Army soldiers toasting the memory of their fallen
comrade and saluting his grave site. (FIRST EXPECTED RUN 1830 NORTH
AMERICA UPDATE)
