<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Golf-Compaq Open </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World No. 1 Sorenstam leads Alfredsson by two strokes
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MALMO, Sweden (AP) _ Annika Sorenstam shot her second straight
71 Saturday and took a 2-stroke lead over fellow Swedish (U.S.)
LPGA star Helen Alfredsson after the penultimate round of the
Compaq Open.
	   Sorenstam, who won the European Tour event on another Swedish
course near her hometown of Stockholm last year, had a 4-under-par
total of 212 going into Sunday's fourth round on the tough
Barseback course.
	   ``But a two-stroke lead is nothing in this wind,'' said
Sorenstam, a two-time former U.S. Open champion ranked No. 1 in the
world. ''Anything can happen, already on the first hole. Helen is a
tough competitor. If she gets a good start, she's difficult to
beat.''
	   Alfredsson, who won the 1993 Dinah Shore for her only major
triumph, had a 70 Saturday and was one shot ahead of Johanna Head
of Britain.
	   Head, who has not made a cut all season, played alongside
Sorenstam in the final group and took the lead with birdies on the
short second _ where she nearly holed in one _ and the third. But
she dropped back with six bogeys to only one more birdie and
finished with a 74 for a 215 total.
	   Laura Davies, the big-hitting British star who's looking for a
Swedish double after winning the Chrysler Open in Goteborg a month
ago, also had a second successive 71 and was alone in fourth place
at 216.
	   Kelly Robbins, the top American in the tournament, slipped to a
77 and shared seventh at 219. She broke the course record with a 67
Saturday.
	   Karrie Webb of Australia shot a 73 for a 220 total. Two former
U.S. Open champions, Alison Nicholas of Britain and Liselotte
Neumann of Sweden, also struggled. Nicholas had a 75-223, Neumann
74-224.
	   Pia Nilsson, Swedish captain of Europe's Solheim Cup team, will
announce her five wild card-entries for the match against the U.S.
defending champions after the tournament ends Sunday. The Solheim
Cup is scheduled Sept. 18-20 at Muirfield Village, Ohio.
	   (sn) 	   
</TEXT>
