<HEADLINE>
BULLETIN
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Angolan troops invade western Congo, back government forces &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: COMBINES pvs. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   GOMA, Congo (AP) _ Angolan troops entered the war against
Congolese rebels on Saturday, landing troops in the west of the
country, a rebel leader said.
	   ``Angolan troops have invaded Congo,'' Bizima Karaha said from
the eastern stronghold of Goma.
	   Karaha said he had no details, but warned that the Angolan
involvement will complicate the crisis and the rebel will hit back
at the attackers.
	   Zimbabwe has already deployed troops to help Congo President
Laurent Kabila ward off rebel advances on the capital, Kinshasa.
	   ``We are calling upon the people of Congo to hold the
aggression,'' Karaha said. ``Angolans must come to their senses and
remove forces from Congo immediately.''
	   ``This involvement has put chances for negotiated settlement at
very narrow or almost impossible,'' he said.
</TEXT>
