<SLUG> BC-Albania-Arrests, 2nd Ld </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police arrests ten foreigners in an anti-terrorist operation
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with large police turnout in Tirana in graf 5. &QL; 
 &UR; By MERITA DHIMGJOKA &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) _ Police and secret service agents arrested
Friday night ten foreigners, including some Arab citizens, after
raiding several houses believed to have served as bases for
terrorist suspects, informed sources reported Saturday.
	   ``All of them were sleeping in one room when police broke in and
searched the apartment where they found bulletproof vests, fake
passports, maps, radio transmitters, electronic devices'' and other
material, said a police source who took part in the operation,
speaking on condition of anonymity.
	   The same source said the ten were Arab citizens, but another
source told The Associated Press later that those arrested also
included citizens from non-Arab countries.
	   The state news agency ATA also reported that ten foreign
citizens had been detained, but it did not give their nationalities
or other details.
	   By Saturday evening, police seemed everywhere in Tirana, the
Albanian capital. Police cars and vans, many of them driving at low
speed, were moving in the pot-holed streets in unusually large
numbers. There was no official explanation for the large turnout.
