<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-du Maurier, 1st Ld-Writethru,0196 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Seles downs Hingis in du Maurier semifinals
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: REPEATING to RESTORE writethru designation; UPDATES with
Saturday's first semifinal. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTREAL (AP) _ Monica Seles of the United States upset
top-seeded Martina Hingis of Switzerland with a 4-6, 6-3, 6-2
semifinal victory Saturday at the dlrs 1.3 million du Maurier Open
women's tennis championship.
	   Hingis, 17, did not lose a service game until Seles, 24, broke
for a 5-3 lead in the second set in the one hour 32 minute match on
the hard court at Montreal's Jarry Stadium.
	   Seles' service games were laborious, hitting on few first serves
early in the match, but she turned that around, breaking for a 2-1
lead and again for 4-1 in the third set.
	   ``I really started to play well as the match went on,'' Seles
said. ``I actually think she was lucky to win the first set ...
Everything just went well for me today.''
	   Seles, the fifth seed, has won the last three du Maurier
tournaments.
	   The second semifinal later Saturday had second-seeded Jana
Novotna of the Czech Republic facing third-seeded Arantxa Sanchez
Vicario of Spain.
</TEXT>
