<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Greek Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Olympiakos beats Apollon at the season's start
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Serbian striker Ilja Ivic scored twice
Saturday as defending champion Olympiakos Piraeus trounced Apollon
Athens 5-2 in a game which signaled the kickoff of the Greek first
division soccer league season.
	   A total of four games involving teams participating in European
tournaments on next week, were played Saturday. The other five
matches of the first round will be played Sunday.
	   Olympiakos and Panathinaikos Athens play in the Champions League
Wednesday, and PAOK Salonica and AEK Athens in the UEFA cup
Tuesday.
	   Olympiakos dominated the first half of the game scoring four
goals and losing at least five other scoring chances. The hosts, on
the other hand, had only one shot against the visitors' goalmouth
during this period.
	   The second period saw Apollon becoming more aggressive scoring
both goals in three minutes
	   The defending champions led with Serbian midfielder Predrag
Djordjevic off a free kick from Grigoris Georgatos in the 16th
minute and Ghanaian Peter Oforiquaye made it 2-0 in the 30th.
	   Two consecutive goals by Ivic in the last four minutes of the
half, increased the score to 4-0. Vassilis Karapialis scored
Olympiakos's fifth goal in the 75th.
	   Camerounian striker Nicolas Dikoume in the 56th and Antonis
Damigos in the 59th minutes were the scorers for the hosts.
	   Serbian defender Vladan Milojevic converted a penalty kick
seconds before the end of a game, to give Panathinaikos a 2-1
victory over Paniliakos Pyrgos.
	   Playing at the Athens Olympic stadium, Panathinaikos was jeered
by its fans, when Paniliakos in its second attack against
Panathinaikos' goalmouth, took the lead with Giannis Tatsis in the
27th minute.
	   Norwegian midfielder Frank Strandli levelled off a cross from
Polish striker Krzysztof Warzycha in the 75th.
	   Panathinaikos launched one attack after the other for a second
goal, but the Paniliakos defense resisted everything until the 45th
when Milojevic scored the winner.
 &UR; kc	   
</TEXT>
