<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Boxing-Brewer-Byrd </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Charles Brewer stops Byrd to defend IBF title
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LEIPZIG, Germany (AP) _ Charles Brewer of the United States
stopped another American, Antoine Byrd, in the third round Saturday
with a flurry of punches to defend his IBF supermiddleweight title.
	   The hard-punching Brewer, who knocked out South Africa's Gary
Ballard a year ago to gain the belt, battered Byrd with a series of
hooks midway through the round.
	   The referee stopped the fight with 1:11 remaining as Brewer
defended his crown for the third time. His record improved to 32-5
with 22 knockouts.
	   Brewer's next title defense will be against Germany's Sven
Ottke, who outpointed Dutchman William Krijnen over 10 rounds on
the same card.
	   Brewer will fight Ottke, a former two-time European amatuer
champion, on Oct. 24 in Duesseldorf Germany. Ottke ran his record
to 12-0 with an unspectacular win over the Dutchman, who took a
standing count in the 10th round.
	   Byrd lifted the first two rounds of the fight against Brewer
before he started to get tagged. It was the Cleverland, Ohio
fighter's third try at winning the same IBF title.
	   Byrd, 31-8 with 17 knockouts, lost a decision to American
Lindell Holmes in 1991 and three years ago to Roy Jones Jr.
	    &UR; (rk)	   
</TEXT>
