<SLUG> BC-Puerto Rico-Weather-Flash Flood Statement,0268 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>

</HEADLINE>
BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD
ADVISORY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
416 PM AST SAT AUG 22 1998

BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD
ADVISORY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
416 PM AST SAT AUG 22 1998

...A URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY IN IN EFFECT UNTIL 600 PM
   FOR THE SOUTH...INTERIOR AND NORTH CENTRAL SECTIONS OF PUERTO
   RICO. THIS INCLUDES ALL MUNICIPALITIES INSIDE A BOX CONNECTING
   VEGA BAJA TO CANOVANAS TO ARROYO TO JUANA DIAZ NORTH TO VEGA
   ALTA...


AT 355 PM...DOPPLER RADAR INDICATED THAT HEAVY SHOWERS AND
THUNDERSTORMS CONTINUED TO DEVELOP ACROSS THE SOUTH AND INTERIOR
SECTIONS OF PUERTO RICO AND MOVE NORTH ACROSS THE NORTHERN SECTIONS
OF THE ISLAND. HEAVY RAIN HAS ALREADY OCCURRED ACROSS THIS AREA
AND ADDITIONAL RAINFALL IS EXPECTED.

ALTHOUGH THERE HAVE BEEN NO REPORTS OF FLOODING...LOCALIZED
STORM..STREET AND ROAD FLOODING IS LIKEY ACROSS THE ADVISORY AREA.
THEREFORE AN URBAN AND SMALL STREAM ADVISORY HAS BEEN ISSUED UNTIL 6
PM.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE ADVISORY AREA
THROUGH 600 PM SHOULD AVOID CROSSING FLOODED ROADS...AND ALLOW
EXTRA TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS. REMEMBER...CARS
CAN EASILY STALL IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY IN ANY CURRENT.
PEDESTRIANS ARE ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM RISING CREEKS. KEEP
CHILDREN AWAY FROM OPEN STORM DRAINS. AVOID AREAS OF STEEP TERRAIN
WHERE MUDSLIDES ARE POSSIBLE.
 &HT;    
