<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Greek Roundup,0323 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Olympiakos beats Apollon at the season's start
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Serbian striker Ilja Ivic scored twice
Saturday as defending champion Olympiakos Piraeus defeated Apollon
Athens 5-2 in the opening game of the Greek first division soccer
league season.
	   A total of four games were played Saturday involving teams
participating in European tournaments next week. The other five
matches of the first round will be played Sunday.
	   Panathinaikos Athens defeated Paniliakos Pyrgos 2-1 after
Serbian defender Vladan Milojevic converted a penalty kick seconds
before the end of a game.
	   Ionikos defeated PAOK Salonika 1-0 and AEK Athens beat Panionios
3-1.
	   Olympiakos and Panathinaikos play in the Champions League
Wednesday, and PAOK and AEK play in the UEFA cup Tuesday.
	   Olympiakos dominated the first half of the game, scoring four
goals and losing at least five other scoring chances while Apollon
had only one shot on goal.
	   The second period saw Apollon becoming more aggressive, scoring
two goals in three minutes, the first by Cameroonian striker
Nicolas Dikoume in the 56th minute and the second by Antonis
Damigos in the 59th.
	   Serbian midfielder Predrag Djordjevic opened the scoring off a
free kick from Grigoris Georgatos in the 16th minute and Ghanaian
Peter Oforiquaye made it 2-0 in the 30th minute.
	   Ivic scored two more goals in the last four minutes of the half.
Vassilis Karapialis scored Olympiakos' fifth goal in the 75th.
	   Playing at the Athens Olympic stadium, Panathinaikos was jeered
by its fans when Paniliakos took the lead with Giannis Tatsis in
the 27th minute.
	   Norwegian midfielder Frank Strandli leveled off a cross from
Polish striker Krzysztof Warzycha in the 75th to even the score.
	   The Paniliakos defense resisted Panathinaikos attacks until the
45th minute, when Milojevic scored the winner.
</TEXT>
