<HEADLINE>
Inspired Cambuur holds PSV
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ Newly promoted Cambuur Leeuwarden,
widely predicted to drop directly back to the first division, held
last year's runner-up PSV Eindhoven 1-1 Saturday.
	   Cambuur owed its first point in the Dutch premiership to the
sheer sweat and effort it showed after new captain Andre Ooijer put
PSV ahead just before the break.
	   But it also needed a stroke of luck as Twan Scheepers' left-foot
shot took a wicked deflection to give the midfielder a crucial late
equalizing goal on his debut for Cambuur.
	   It took 70 minutes for Nikos Machlas, the Greek scoring machine
who dominated Dutch football last year with 34 goals, to open his
account for Vitesse Arnhem this season.
	   He finally shook off the close marking which had shut him out of
the game and rose to head home from almost point blank range,
handing Vitesse a 1-0 win over Roda JC.
	   In Saturday's other games MVV Maastricht went down 2-1 at De
Graafschap Doetinchem, AZ Alkmaar downed Sparta Rotterdam 2-0 and
NEC Nijmegen defeated RKC Waalwijk 1-0.
	   Champion Ajax Amsterdam completes the first round of games
Sunday when it plays host to Willem II Tilburg.
