<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Spanish Supercup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mallorca beats Barcelona 1-0 to take Spanish Supercup
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BARCELONA, Spain (AP) _ Mallorca beat Spanish league and cup
champion FC Barcelona by a score of 1-0 Saturday night to take the
Spanish Supercup, the season's first trophy.
	   Mallorca had won the final's first leg 2-1 on Tuesday in Palma.
	   The Supercup is played between the winner of the first division
and the King's Cup. Since Barcelona won both, Mallorca qualified
having been finalist in the King's Cup.
	   Saturday's win marked the first time Mallorca has won a title in
Spanish football.
	   Barcelona dominated for the first 20 minutes or so at the Camp
Nou stadium, keeping Mallorca pinned down with spirited individual
play by Luis Felipe Madeira and Luis Enrique Martinez.
	   But as the game wore on, the Catalan titan found it harder and
harder to gel as a team despite its wealth of talent.
	   In the first half Barcelona led in shots on goal, and threatened
on several occasions, one time forcing Argentine goalkeeper Carlos
Angel Roa to come out and virtually tackle Luis Enrique as he tried
to slam home a shot from just outside the box.
	   Barcelona's best chance came in the 19th minute on a free kick
by Brazilian Rivaldo which sailed just high of the crossbar.
	   The visitors from the Balearic islands finally jumped ahead in
the 29th minute on a crisp header by Daniel Garcia following a pass
from behind him by Francisco Soler.
	   Garcia knocked it in from ten meters (yards) out, just to the
right of diving Barcelona goalkeeper Ruud Hesp.
	   In the 30th minute of the second period Garcia came close to
scoring a second goal, again on a nice header.
	   Spanish first division play begins Aug. 30.
	   (dw)
</TEXT>
