<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-RugbyU-World Cup-Americas, 1st Ld-Writethru,0327 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Americans qualify for World Cup with 21-16 victory over Uruguay
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with Argentina-Canada result; CORRECTS spelling of
Blom, Sharrenberg, Ormaechea, Sciarra. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) _ Andre Blom and Mark Scharrenberg
scored tries and some tactical kicks in the final 10 minutes sent
the United States to the Rugby World Cup with a 21-16 victory over
Uruguay on Saturday.
	   The United States became the third team to qualify for the
20-nation finals in September-October 1999 in Britain, Ireland and
France.
	   In Saturday's other game Argentina routed Canada 54-28 to finish
as the top team in the America's qualifying tournament. Both teams
qualified with victories on Tuesday.
	   The three teams from the Americas join host Wales, defending
champion South Africa, 1995 World Cup runner-up New Zealand and
1995 third-place finisher France in the finals.
	   The loss sends Uruguay into March's repechage qualifying
tournament, a seven-team event involving all five geographical
regions from which two teams will qualify.
	   Blom's try in the 13th and penalties by fly half Mark Williams
in the 32nd and first minute of first-half injury time got the U.S.
Eagles out to a 11-6 lead.
	   Scrum half Federico Sciarra's penalties in the 21st and fourth
minute of first-half injury time were all Uruguay could muster
despite the advantage of the wind on the grounds of the Buenos
Aires Cricket and Rugby Club.
	   Sciarra pulled Uruguay with two points with his his third
penalty goal nine minutes into the second half.
	   But Scharrenberg scored a solo try in the 52nd minute and
Williams added the conversion to put the Americans in control.
	   Captain Diego Ormaechea salvaged Uruguay's pride by pushing over
a try in the 70th minute, but some well-placed kicks in the final
10 minutes kept Uruguay pinned in its half and preserved the U.S.
victory.
</TEXT>
