Angolan troops invade western Congo to back government forces
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS para 2 Angolan gov't source saying troops to defend
Kinshasa.
 &UR; With Zimbabwe-Congo; Congo-Peace Talks
 &UR; AP Photos KIN101-104
 &UR; By HRVOJE HRANJSKI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   GOMA, Congo (AP) _ Rebels battling to topple President Laurent
Kabila on Saturday accused Angola of entering the fray in Congo's
escalating war, which already includes forces from Zimbabwe and
threatens to engulf other African states.
	   An Angolan government source, speaking on condition of
anonymity, said troops would defend Kinshasa, although he gave no
official word on his government's position on the fighting.
