 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   EDGARTOWN, Massachusetts _ The United States escalates the fight
against international terrorism by moving to shut down the
financial pipeline feeding Osama bin Laden's Afghanistan-based
network. US-BOMBINGS. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By Sonya Ross. AP
Photos NAI101, LHR101.
	   NAIROBI, Kenya _ Three jailed suspects reportedly tell police
that with the backing of Osama bin Laden, they ran a phony
fishmongering business as cover in preparing to bomb the U.S.
embassy, a Kenyan newspaper reports. EMBASSY BOMBINGS. RECAP
expected by 0300 GMT. By Laura King. AP Photo NAI101.
	   WASHINGTON _ Osama bin Laden uses his wealth to create cells of
Muslim fighters to cleanse the country of its Soviet occupiers. Now
he's facing battle with an even stronger enemy, one that has
labeled him ``one of the most significant sponsors of Islamic
extremist activities in the world.'' US-SUPERPOWER SUPERENEMY. Has
moved. By Donna Abu-Nasr. AP Photo NY186.
	   KHARTOUM, Sudan _ For Sudan's government, America's missile
barrage on a pharmaceuticals plant near the capital is a rare
opportunity to rally its weary people around the flag. SUDAN-WAR AT
HOME. Has moved. By Anthony Shadid. AP Photos KHT101-108.
