restore programs to help the most vulnerable members of society.
GERMANY-SOCIAL DEMOCRATS. Has moved. By Tony Czuczka. AP Photo
BER101,107.
	   NASSAU, Bahamas _ Bonnie strengthens into the Atlantic season's
first hurricane, a 300-mile-long (482-kilometer-long) storm that
dwarfs sparsely populated Bahamian islands on its route as it heads
toward the southeastern United States. HURRICANE BONNIE. RECAPS
material from Tropical Weather; expected by 0300 GMT. By Jessica
Robertson. AP Photo FLPS 101. AP Graphic.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: On Sunday, Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong
gives `state-of-the-republic' speech.
 &UR; FEATURES: Arts and Entertainment
	   LOS ANGELES _ This summer's movies weren't for the
faint-hearted, what with all the flying meteors, whizzing German
bullets, and that rampaging lizard. And yet people went to see
them. With so much on the menu, however, a few films got buried,
separating losers from winners. ARTS-US-BIG SUMMER. To move as wire
time permits. By Michael Fleeman. AP Photos NY300-NY301
	   DUBAI, United Arab Emirates _ This small ambitious emirate got
the nickname, Hong Kong of the Middle East, for its role as a
commercial hub for the surrounding region. Now it wants to add
another notch to its belt _ Hollywood of the Gulf.
ARTS-UAE-HOLLYWOOD OF THE GULF. To move as wire time permits. By
Faiza Saleh Ambah. AP Photo NY302
	   LOS ANGELES _ Bo Derek had a curious career since her
sensational appearance in 1979 as the object of Dudley Moore's
obsession in ``10.'' Instead of accepting big roles, she worked
only with her husband, John Derek. Derek died this year, and the
actress will appear in a fall TV movie. ARTS-US-BO DEREK. To move
as wire time permits. By Bob Thomas. AP Photo NY303
	   Also Moving:
